  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Other</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>Exercise</intervention_name>
    <description>The intervention will include 2 sessions of gym-based exercise per week, both of which will be supervised for 3 months, supervision will then decrease to once-weekly until 6 months, and then be through phone support for the remaining 6 months. Warm up and cool down of minimum of five minutes on stationary exercise cycle, rate of perceived exertion (RPE) ~11, followed by gentle stretching. Progressive resistance training (PRT) will use eight PRT machines training large muscle groups (e.g. bench press, latissimus pulldown, bicep curl, triceps pull down, leg press, knee extension, hamstring curl, calf raises). Intensity will be 80% of one repetition maximum (1RM), building up to 3 sets of 8 repetitions. 1RM will be re-assessed monthly, and program adjusted accordingly.</description>
    <arm_group_label>Exercise</arm_group_label>
  </intervention>
  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  - Stages 3-4 chronic kidney disease (CKD) patients (glomerular filtration rate (GFR)
             20-60 mL/min)

          -  Male or female

          -  Aged &gt;18 years

          -  Written informed consent

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnancy

               -  Requiring support for ambulation less than 20m

               -  Vasculitis,

               -  Proliferative diabetic retinopathy,

               -  Severe osteodystrophy,

               -  Uncontrolled diabetes,

               -  Psychiatric illness, including anxiety, mood and untreated eating disorders

               -  Infection or course of antibiotics within the last month
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
